<p>I'm using u8glib library - arm edition. I have implemented my I2C handling and I am using eBay (128x64, SSD1306, Yellow/Blue) OLED screen. I'm having the problem with simple u8g_DrawBox(&amp;u8g,0,0,128,64). After the LOOP has finished, screen is black, this is happening because the LOOP does this steps:</p>  <ol> <li>draws first row - 0-8px</li> <li>draws second row - 8-16px</li> <li>draws third row - 16-24px</li> <li>draws fourth row - 24-32px</li> <li>nothing</li> <li>nothing</li> <li>nothing</li> <li>nothing</li> <li>deletes first row - 8px</li> <li>deletes second row - 8px</li> <li>deletes third row - 8px</li> <li>deletes fourth row - 8px</li> </ol>  <p>Can anyone explain this? I'm using device implementation (u8g_dev_ssd1306_128x64_i2c) and my own implementation of communication function (<a href="https://gist.github.com/markoknez/d1430882b67ab9b59a99" rel="nofollow">gist</a>). Btw pixels are approximate of what I could see with magnification.</p>